objects.name: wishful woodchuck
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck is a non-persistent Windows keylogger observed in multiple variants (x86/x64 DLLs and executables). It hooks the keyboard via Windows API calls (SetWindowsHookExW), captures keystrokes, and logs them to an encoded file (msimm.dat) using a static multi-byte rotating XOR key embedded in the binary. The log format includes a header (KSL0, TVer=21.0, Start, and the current username) and per-line metadata (timestamp, window handle, process ID/name, window title) followed by keystrokes. The malware dynamically resolves API imports with names obfuscated via XOR 0x55 and uses multi-byte XOR obfuscation for internal strings and log file contents. Some samples masquerade with filenames resembling legitimate Windows binaries (e.g., lmm32.dll vs imm32.dll) and use a TVer versioning string previously associated with Turla. It contains no persistence or network communications functionality; execution lasts only while the host is running. An executable dropper (msvrt.exe) can deploy the DLL and invoke exported functions (SetHook, SetWinCheck).

objects.name: Turla
objects.description: The report notes that Wishful Woodchuck contains capabilities previously observed in use by the Turla threat group, including use of a TVer versioning string and XOR 0x55 obfuscation of Windows API function names. These overlaps suggest the keylogger was likely written by Turla.

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Finds binaries containing the hardcoded XOR key
from the keylogger binaries"

    strings:
        $xorkey = {0A 19 59 2D 6C 59 6F FA 8B 6F 9B FF 37 9B BD 7B 59 4B
7B DD 0F 64 91 C7 D6 9C 6F 7B 9C 01 9C 91 79 C7 C8 C9 DF E1 FA FF 04 08
59 E6 64 6D 37 9B 38 81 2D 81 65 7D 66 9A}

    condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

all of them

}

rule wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader

        author = "NCSC"

46}
    condition:
        all of them
}
